<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-03-31T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-03-31T13:00:00-05:00" n="297" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d297">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00 Nanking/246: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Cunningham</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-03-31T13:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">March 31,
                                        1928—1 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>For the Minister: Minister’s telegrams March 30, 3 p.m. and 8 p.m.</p>
                        <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>Very much gratified, the Department extends to you congratulations
                                upon successful outcome of your efforts.</item>
                            <pb facs="0452" n="334" xml:id="pg_334"/>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>It is assumed that you will remain temporarily in Shanghai.</item>
                            <label>3.</label>
                            <item>There will be sent to you shortly the Department’s comments in
                                regard to the proposed notes and replies.</item>
                        </list>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>